Message from the Health Department:

For shorter wait times at our drive thru COVID 19 site at Wheeler County Health Department, please pre-register. You can pre-register one of two ways:
1. Click here https://covid19.dph.ga.gov. An email address is required. You will receive a QR code via email that you will need to bring to the site.
2. Call 478-275-6570 Monday-Friday 8-5 and Saturday 9-2. They can help you register over the phone.

If you do not pre-register, you can still be tested. You may just have a longer wait time.

post_text: Parade in honor of our basketball State Champs!

post_text:
Message from Coach Wright:

ATTENTION WHEELER COUNTY AND SURROUNDING COUNTIES!!! On Saturday, August 29th, we are having a drive-by parade for our girls 2019-2020 Class A Public State Basketball Champions starting at 12 noon! Please meet up at the Town Square around 11:45 a.m. in Alamo and get in line and follow the law enforcement personnel through the approved route. Because of COVID-19 we will not be able to have a regular style parade! But you, our loyal fans, have the opportunity to make signs and banners to display as you drive by our girls as they stand on the steps of the James Stapleton gymnasium. They will have a small bag just in case some of you may want to bless them in your own way! We have waited so long to honor them. Covid has caused us to modify our celebration and our recognition ceremony. So please take advantage of this opportunity to show them some love and appreciation! Join us on Saturday as a participant in the parade!

post_text:
Reminder of the 2020-2021 dress code for Wheeler County Middle/High School:

Middle/High School Dress Code

Requirements:

-All shorts and skirts must be knee length.

-Pants/shorts/skirts must be secured around the natural waistline, with a belt if necessary.

-All clothing items must be properly fastened (shoes, belts, etc.).

-Masks must follow dress code requirements below.

-Neck gaiters must be WCSS-supplied ones or solid in color.

NOT Allowed:

-Leggings will not be allowed.

-No holes or shredding of any kind in jeans or pants.

-No gym shorts, sweatpants, or athletic pants.

-No sagging pants/shorts.

-No tank tops, midriffs, halter tops, mesh tops, or see-through garments.

-No clothing with offensive symbols or phrases.

-No clothing with gang-related symbols or phrases.

-No clothing displaying tobacco alcohol, or drug-related advertisements, illustrations, or phrases.

-No caps or sunglasses inside the building.

-No headware, bandanas, headscarves, or dog chains.

-No body piercing of any kind. (This does not include earrings).

-No pajamas.

-No blankets.

Wheeler County School System is accepting applications for a school nurse (LPN or RN) for Wheeler County Middle High School (to serve grades 6-12). Application available here: https://www.wheelercountyschools.org/pdf/non%20certified.pdf
Applications are due by noon on 7/22/2020 and can be submitted by any of the following methods:

Email completed application to suzanne.couey@wheeler.k12.ga.us

Fax completed application to (912) 568-7198

Submit in person at WCSS Board Office (18 McRae Street; Alamo, GA).

post_text:
ATTENTION Class of 2020:
Some information about recordings for graduation ceremony: They are only going to be about 10 seconds long, not speeches or anything formal…just maybe your name and what you plan to do in the fall, or who you want to thank for helping you get through school. The recordings will be informal and done by school or district staff, so nothing to be nervous about. We can re-film your clip if you don’t like the first version, and no one except the few school or district employees filming will be watching. The only students that will have formal speeches are Lindsey and Towns. If you absolutely don’t want to do a recording, we can use your drape picture from the yearbook. If you have questions, email Mrs. Couey.

shared_text:
2020CENSUS.GOV
2020 Census | United States Census Bureau

William Brandon Pope
April 21 at 7:37 PM ·

CENSUS 2020 UPDATE: If you haven't responded yet, now is the time. It's easy! You can do it online, by phone, or by using a paper form.

Respond online by going to www.2020census.gov; by phone by dialing 1-844-330-2020 (English) or 1-844-468-2020 (Espanol). *Please encourage at least 10 people you know to complete the Census.

Since we are not able to host any events at this time, the best way to get the word our about completing the Census is by word of mouth. *As of yesterday the response rate for the Tri-County area for the Census: Treutlen County, 41.5%, Montgomery County, 31.9%, Wheeler, 22%, compared to the state of Georgia average of 47.9%.

We will have the following changes to our dress code for the 2020-2021 school year:
No holes or shredding in pants (jeans or otherwise)
No leggings, sweat pants, jogging pants, or athletic pants
Skirts must be at the knee or longer
Shorts will be worn at knee length for middle/high, but no gym/athletic shorts will be allowed at all, except for PE.

SENIORS now is the time to apply to college. It's the silver lining during these uncertain times.

Current high school seniors who have not applied to or have not submitted test scores for admissions to Georgia State University Atlanta, will be evaluated based on GPA only.
The minimum (recalculated) GPA for acceptance to the GSU Atlanta campus is 3.0
To be accepted into the GSU Atlanta campus through Success Academy the GPA (recalculated) is 2.5-2.99
Students with a GPA below of 2.5 (recalculated) will be deferred to the GSU Perimeter campus

Frequently Asked Questions for Students and Parents

Please refer to the linked document for answers to frequently asked questions:
Frequently Asked Questions for Students and Parents

Two of the questions and answers are included below for quick reference:

Where can I submit a question?
From your computer, visit our website (www.wheelercountyschools.org ). In the middle of the far right of the page, you will see a tab that says “Contact Us.” Click on it and complete the form OR click on “2020 Information,” the top right tab on our home page, scroll down to “Contact” and submit your question there.

Where is the best place to find information about Wheeler County Schools?
Information will be updated on our webpage under News and Announcements (middle of page) and under 2020 Information (top right tab) in the following sections: For Students, For Parents, and COVID-19 Information. We will also provide call outs for important information.

To limit the spread of COVID-19 and protect the public, the Division of Family and Children Services (DFCS) encourages families to access self-service options online during this period.

Self-service options include:
Apply for Food Stamp and Medicaid Benefits
Visit: gateway.ga.gov (verification documents can also be uploaded and case status info is available for all benefits)
Download an Application:
https://dfcs.georgia.gov/services
Electronic Benefits Transfer (EBT)
Visit: https://www.connectebt.com/gaebtclient or call: 888-421-3281 for updates

Those without internet access can contact the DFCS Customer Contact Center at 877-423-4746 for additional information or to request a paper application. Once completed, applications and any required verification can be mailed back to your local county DFCS office. County office locations are available online at https://dfcs.georgia.gov/locations.

post_text:
Information for families needing help with teaching your children at home.

Faced with an unprecedented scenario, Georgia’s districts, schools, teachers, and families are finding creative ways to stay connected with students through distance and virtual learning.
GaDOE’s Curriculum and Instruction team and Georgia Public Broadcasting (GPB) Education Division have partnered to launch the Georgia Home Classroom initiative, which includes instructional TV broadcasts aligned to Georgia’s state standards, along with a library of digital learning resources.

https://www.gpb.org/education/learn
For free online courses for those new to virtual learning and for instructional resources organized by content area: https://www.gadoe.org/External-Affairs-and-Policy/communications/Pages/Digital-Learning-Resources.aspx

To help us plan and possibly provide resources, we need some information from parents regarding internet service and computer access in our students' homes.

Please complete the internet survey using the following link or QR code. Please complete only ONE survey and include the names of ALL Wheeler County School Students in your home (grades PK-12)

post_text: Mrs. L. Adams' Algebra 1 class is learning about lines and linear equations using a new on-line resource called Flocabulary. Each lesson is introduced with a song. This lesson's song describes various properties of lines. They don’t curve and only cross the x-axis and y-axis once each. The song also explains linear equations, x-intercept and y-intercept, slope, and how to find the slope-intercept form of a linear equation. Students completed vocab cards, a vocab game and finished off with assessment.

post_text: Congratulations to our Literary Team. They placed 5th overall today while competing in Vidalia. Individual results are as follows: Jasmine Holland Soto – Girls Solo (4th place); Amber Seabolt – Domestic Extemporaneous Speaking (3rd place); Gabrielle Myrick – International Extemporaneous Speaking (1st place); Jaci Hill – Dramatic Oral Interpretation (3rd place); Tegan Rigdon – Argumentative Essay; Karmin Clark – Personal Essay; and Kimberlyn Stinson – Rhetorical Essay (2nd place). Gabrielle and Kimberlyn will advance to the state Literary Meet in Milledgeville on March 14. Special thanks to the advisor, Mr. Phil Parker!

post_text: This month WCHS is also celebrating CTAE month. Career, Technical, and Agriculture Education at our school consists of several different pathways. One of those pathways is the Business and Technology Pathway with our own Mrs. April Logue. This pathway contains three classes: Introduction to Business and Technology, Business and Technology, and Business Communications. After completion of these three classes, students must pass an assessment in Microsoft Office Specialist in either Powerpoint, Excel, or Word. Students that pass receive a cord that they wear at graduation.

post_text:
NEW SCHOLARSHIP: Telfair American Legion Veterans – P.O.W.’s Scholarship Award
1. Applicant must be a graduating high school senior.
2. Applicant must live in Georgia.
3. Applicant must be sponsored by a Georgia Department of the American Legion Post.
4. Academic requirements include student’s accumulated grade point average, class ranking, and standardized test scores. Official records must be furnished for senior year.
5. Applicant must have participated in school and community activities.
6. Applicant must provide transcript of grades. Transcript must be official document from school in a sealed envelope.
7. A scholarship will be awarded for $1,000.
8. Applications must be received by March 16, 2020
9. Applicant must have an endorsement from the sponsoring Post 80 and high school principal.
10. Applications must be returned to The American Legion, Post 80; McRae, GA.

post_text: Mrs. Logue's class did a semester long business simulation project. Students had to come up with their own Food Truck concept and work throughout the semester on it. They discussed some parts of a Business Plan, developed a Marketing Plan, Brand Recognition (Logo, Slogans, Color/Font Schemes, Food Truck Design), created a Menu, Advertising Mediums and Techniques, and Business Pitch. The students had to work as a TEAM to create everything. At the end of this project, the teams should "pitch" their business ideas to the class and "guest investors" in a "Shark Tank" style presentation. Each team got $5,000 of imaginary money to invest in 1 Food Truck (other than their own) and guest investors each got $25,000 to invest in one or multiple Food Trucks. The group with the most money will win the competition.

post_text: This week, Mr. Pope's class was pleased to welcome Kim David, Vice President of Economic Development at OFTC. Ms. David gave valuable insight to a number of students about economic development in our area, potential financial aid in high need job areas, and the benefits of vocational and technical education. The students would like to let Ms. David know how much they appreciate her taking time out of her busy schedule to come and be with them.

Today begins our annual Apply To College Week. This is the week when the focus is to have every senior complete at least one college application. We have sixteen colleges coming to help seniors fill out any college application. The list is as follows:
Monday: Georgia Southern, Albany State, South Georgia College
Tuesday: Georgia Military College, Savannah State, College of Coastal Georgia, East Georgia, Valdosta, and Gordon State
Wednesday: Middle Georgia ad Andrew College
Thursday: Georgia College, Georgia Southwestern, and Georgia State
Friday: University of Georgia (Griffin Campus), and Clayton State

post_text: The Wheeler County FFA Land Judging Team recently placed 2nd overall at the State CDE held at Ft.Valley State University. This is the highest placing a team from Wheeler FFA has earned. The team was comprised of 4 members, Lindsey Grimes who was the 2nd high scoring individual overall at the contest, Cole Smith who was 4th high individual, Towns Etheredge and David Clark. This group of FFA members qualified for state by winning first place in the Area IV CDE held in September. Wheeler’s Jr. team comprised of 9th grade members also finished 4th overall at state as well. The Jr. team members included Amber Seabolt who was the 6th high individual, Lily Parker, Owen Stokes and Marlee Veal.

post_text: Prayers from Wheeler County High School!
shared_text:
Johnson County Schools
October 29, 2019 at 10:26 AM ·

It is with great regret and sorrow that we inform you that one of our beloved coaches, teacher, and best friend was in an accident this morning. Coach Shawn Linder and his daughter Bella did not survive the accident. His death is a loss to our school and community. He was a Johnson County Alumni, husband, father, valued friend, and brother. He loved kids and was a friend to all. Please keep Natalie, Brayden, Ms. Sharon Linder, and the entire family in your prayers.

We have several school counselors, pastors, and mental health counselors, and other health care professionals to assist our family in this time of grief.

Our principal, Dr. Watkins, will excuse any absence today
if you feel the need to sign your child out.

post_text: Beta Club is selling pink ribbons for Breast Cancer Awareness Month! Ribbons are 25 cents; all proceeds will be donated to the American Cancer Society. When you buy a ribbon, you can decorate it in honor or in memory of someone special or you can write a message of hope on it. Decorated ribbons will be displayed in the front lobby of the school. Help your class win this homecoming competition as well by buying your pink ribbon from any Beta member of Mr. Parker.

post_text: As part of the Homecoming competition for 2019, Beta Club is holding a Canned Food Drive. The class that donates the most canned food by 10:00 on Friday, October 25, will receive the most points in the class competition. All canned food must be nonperishable and unopened; items that are beyond expiration date will be discarded and will not count. (In order to receive homecoming points, your class must donate a minimum of 25 items.)

post_text:
Unfortunately, our annual trip to OFTC for the Probe Fair is during our fall break on Tuesday, October 15th. Our juniors and seniors are still welcomed to attend on their own anytime between 9 to 11 am.
Probe is an annual program of college fairs that are held throughout the state of Georgia. The program is managed by the Georgia Education Articulation Committee (GEAC), whose sole mission is to disseminate information and stimulate interest in post-secondary education for students in Georgia. Hundreds of colleges from across the nation attend Probe each year to reach thousands of Georgia high school juniors and seniors.
Click here to view the college tour schedule: http://www.gaprobe.org/probe-tour-calendar/
